==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hyphenated American
<hw>Hyphenated American</hw>. <def>An American who is referred to by a
hyphenated term with the first word indicating an origin in a foreign
country, and the second term being ⟦ldquo⟧American⟦rdquo⟧, as
<stype>Irish-American</stype>, <stype>Italian-American</stype>,
<stype>African-American</stype>, <stype>Asian-American</stype>.</def>
<mark>Used in reference to Americans of foreign birth or ancestry. When
used of Americans of European ancestry, it is often used to refer to
those who have a strong attachment to the ancestral country or its
culture. It implies that the individual is imperfectly assimilated into
American culture, and is sometimes used derogatively.</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hyphomycetes</ent>⟦br⟧
